  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 23 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 5 critical, 12 high, 12 medium, 10 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 14 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, low cloud base and mist  — most notably around Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE) and Craiova (CRA/LRCV). Network hotspots: Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Brussels South Charleroi (CRL/EBCI), Cologne Bonn (CGN/EDDK), Nuremberg (NUE/EDDN), Stuttgart (STR/EDDS) and 18 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and thunderstorm / convective risk. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Brussels South Charleroi (CRL/EBCI), Nuremberg (NUE/EDDN) and 9 others.",
